<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7314> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7314" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 71. Procos. 76, MRR 2.93, and 96, note 4. From this note, R. E. Smith (Service in the Post-Marian Roman Army 17, note 9) would remove the reference to IG 12.5.722, on the ground that the title # can refer only to the pre-Sullan Aufidius of ca. 107, 106 (see MRR 1.551, 552, note 2, 553). On the adoptive name and status of Orestes, see Shackleton Bailey, Studies 84-85; Sumner, Orators 46, 82.\n" ;
	dprr:hasID 7314 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3516> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3516" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Propraetor ({Gr}, IG 12.5.722) in Asia. See 107, Praetors, and note 2." ;
	dprr:hasID 3516 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3496> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3496" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Fin. 5.54; Tusc. 5.112; cf. Dom. 35, and Cons. fr. 19 (ed. Müller)." ;
	dprr:hasID 3496 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3495> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3495" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See 106, Promagistrates; and note IG 12.5.722. See also 77, Praetors, and 76, Promagistrates. This praetorship is placed conjecturally about 107 by Waddington, Fasti des provinces asiatiques, p. 666, and Chapot, Prov. rom. procons. Asie 307. It may have followed or preceded that of Billienus." ;
	dprr:hasID 3495 .
